headline.main: CITY AND COUNTY AFFAIRS.; BOARD OF ALDERMEN. APPOINTMENTS.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Board met at 5 o'clock, P.M., on Monday, Alderman GENET in the chair. The City Inspector sent a communication announcing the appointment of Nathaniel Dee, Health Warden in place of B.B. Chappell, removed; of John Kelly, of the Thirteenth Ward, in place of Thomas J. Carleton, resigned.
